  <graph edgedefault="directed">
    <node id="start" />
    <node id="Convert the proposed arrangement from a lease-like commitment into a lender-safe, time-bounded “License + Storm-Season Continuity Addendum” that is (a) publicly announceable this week, (b) sufficient to satisfy the grant’s site-stability/privacy/relocation requirements, and (c) preserves an explicit developer exit path without mid-storm disruption." />
    <node id="Finalize lender-approved license term sheet + exhibits for signature and public announcement" />
    <node id="Lock open variables (standstill tail + relocation cap) and obtain lender counsel sign-off for signature package" />
    <node id="lender_counsel_bracket_selection_and_signature_package" />
    <node id="Secure a lender-approved, announcement-safe ‘Track A’ package (nonbinding term sheet + Storm-Season Continuity Addendum summary + PHI/no-lease certification + Exhibit E press/signage language) that City Emergency Management can use publicly this week without implying a lease, while preserving the path to execute the full interim license immediately after counsel triage." />
    <node id="Assemble_and_get_lender_greenlight_for_Track_A_announcement_package" />
    <node id="Secure lender-counsel “green light to announce” this week via an announcement-only, nonbinding public-facing packet that (a) avoids any lease/tenancy signals, and (b) still satisfies the storm-season grant’s documentation needs (site stability through Nov 30, privacy controls, and a workable relocation path)." />
